ExecutorCommands.ShutdownNow - Class in com.starsoft.plib.executors.commands
When passing an instance of this class as parameter "processor" to fun processing in class SequentiallyProcessorExecutor the executor stops working Attempts to stop all actively executing tasks, halts the processing of waiting tasks, and returns a list of the tasks that were awaiting execution in the onProcessedCallback call if it is presented. These tasks are drained (removed) from the task queue.

S

SequentiallyProcessorExecutor - Class in com.starsoft.plib.executors
Starts implementation off interface Processor to run sequentially using a pool of threads with a single thread, tasks that do not come from the main thread are rejected, can be controlled by passing special commands in the processing parameter "onProcessedCallback" see class ExecutorCommands after received command class ExecutorCommands.ShutdownNow all new tasks are rejected if the processing onProcessedCallback parameter was passed when calling the command class ExecutorCommands.ShutdownNow the list of outstanding tasks will be returned in it for correct processing of the class ExecutorCommands.ShutdownNow all of the processor implementation must include verification interrupt by isInterrupted and ensure that work is completed correctly
